title: Bindi Irwin goes 'Dirty Dancing' with the Stars
text:
CNN Leadership
'Dancing With the Stars': Bindi Irwin does 'Dirty Dancing' Updated 1526 GMT (2226 HKT) October 20, 2015 14 photos: 'Dancing With the Stars' season 21 Wildlife conservationist Bindi Irwin, daughter of the late Crocodile Hunter Steve Irwin, has captivated audiences with her professional partner, Derek Hough, on season 21 of "Dancing With the Stars." Click through to meet the rest of the dance pairs. Hide Caption 1 of 14 14 photos: 'Dancing With the Stars' season 21 Backstreet Boy Nick Carter and pro partner Sharna Burgess are also in contention in this season's competition. Hide Caption 2 of 14 14 photos: 'Dancing With the Stars' season 21 Reality and producer Tamar Braxton doesn't always like to follow directions from pro partner and season 20 champ Valentin Chmerkovskiy. Still, their chemistry and moves are putting them in contention. Hide Caption 3 of 14 14 photos: 'Dancing With the Stars' season 21 Alexa PenaVega is part of the first married couple to compete -- against each other -- in the dance competition. She is professionally partnered with Mark Ballas, and judges have loved their recent moves. Hide Caption 14 photos: 'Dancing With the Stars' season 21 Teen social media sensation Hayes Grier is paired with pro dancer Emma Slater. Hide Caption 5 of 14 14 photos: 'Dancing With the Stars' season 21 Alek Skarlatos, one of the heroes who stopped a terror attack on a French train over the summer, is dancing with pro Lindsay Arnold. Hide Caption 6 of 14 14 photos: 'Dancing With the Stars' season 21 Host Tom Bergeron, left, chats with Carlos PenaVega and pro partner Witney Carson. PenaVega's wife, Alexa, is also competing on the show -- against him. Hide Caption 14 photos: 'Dancing With the Stars' season 21 Singer Andy Grammer, center, and pro partner Allison Holker are shown with Bergeron. Hide Caption 8 of 14 14 photos: 'Dancing With the Stars' season 21 Chef Paula Deen, who was partnered with Louis Van Amstel, was voted off in week five of the show. Hide Caption 14 photos: 'Dancing With the Stars' season 21 Gary Busey, who was paired with Anna Trebunskaya, was voted off in week four. Hide Caption 10 of 14 14 photos: 'Dancing With the Stars' season 21 "Real Housewives" reality star Kim Zolciak Biermann, who was partnered with Tony Dovolani, had to leave the show during week three because of medical issues. Hide Caption 11 of 14 14 photos: 'Dancing With the Stars' season 21 Winning jockey Victor Espinoza, who was partnered with Karina Smirnoff, couldn't win with a human partner. He was voted off in week two of the show. Hide Caption 12 of 14 14 photos: 'Dancing With the Stars' season 21 Singer Chaka Khan, who was partnered with Keo Motsepe, was voted off the show in week two. Hide Caption 13 of 14 14 photos: 'Dancing With the Stars' season 21 The "Dancing with the Stars" season 21 judges are Carrie Ann Inaba, left, Julianne Hough and Bruno Tonioli. Hide Caption
